{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016gE9VKuk8EzjPbc2EhgRWT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013cxGpazPSNB3uwVGEdGkiq","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'REPORT'\nRAY NAMESPACE CONFIGURATION AUDIT REPORT\n=========================================\nAudit Date : 2026-06-16\nNamespace  : ray\nAuditor    : read-only inspection (no cluster changes made)\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nDeployment   : ray-worker\nCurrent      : 3 replicas (3/3 ready)\nBaseline     : 2 replicas  (from last-applied-configuration annotation)\nSTATUS       : [DEVIATION] +1 replica above baseline\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n2. IMAGE VERSIONS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nray-head     : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nray-worker   : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nBaseline     : rayproject/ray:2.9.0 (both)\nSTATUS       : [OK] Images match baseline; no upgrade detected\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nray-head     : resources: {}  (no requests or limits)\nray-worker   : resources: {}  (no requests or limits)\nBaseline     : resources: {}  (same — no change from baseline)\nSTATUS       : [OK vs baseline] Unchanged; however see compliance note below\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n4. EXPOSED SERVICES\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nService      : ray-head (ClusterIP 10.96.200.15)\nCurrent ports:\n  - gcs       : 6379/TCP\n  - dashboard : 8265/TCP  <-- ADDED vs baseline\nBaseline ports:\n  - gcs       : 6379/TCP  (only)\nSTATUS       : [DEVIATION] Dashboard port 8265 was added to the Service\n\nray-head Deployment command change (correlated):\n  Baseline : --include-dashboard=false  (no dashboard containerPort)\n  Current  : --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0\n             containerPort 8265 (dashboard) added to pod spec\nSTATUS       : [DEVIATION] Dashboard enabled and bound to 0.0.0.0 inside pod\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n5. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nkube-root-ca.crt    : system default (present in all namespaces)\nrollback-rehearsal  : non-default; contains a rollback script that\n                      independently documents the two deviations found\n                      above (replicas 3→2 and removal of port 8265).\n                      This ConfigMap was present at audit time.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n6. POD STATUS SUMMARY\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nray-head-7c665f5784-q6vmc     : Running 1/1 — 0 restarts\nray-worker-7d7d685797-4h8xz   : Running 1/1 — 1 restart\nray-worker-7d7d685797-fkqdw   : Running 1/1 — 1 restart\nray-worker-7d7d685797-h5c5k   : Running 1/1 — 1 restart\nray-client                    : Running 1/1 — 0 restarts\ncurl-test                     : Running 1/1 — 0 restarts\nNOTE: Each ray-worker pod shows 1 restart; likely due to the replica scale-up\n      or head restart before the dashboard patch stabilised.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n7. DEVIATION SUMMARY\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n#  Component              Field                 Baseline  Current\n1  ray-worker Deployment  spec.replicas         2         3\n2  ray-head Deployment    --include-dashboard   false     true\n2  ray-head Deployment    --dashboard-host      (absent)  0.0.0.0\n2  ray-head Deployment    containerPort 8265    absent    present\n2  ray-head Service       port dashboard:8265   absent    present\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n8. COMPLIANCE NOTES & RECOMMENDATIONS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n[HIGH] Dashboard exposed on 0.0.0.0:8265 without authentication.\n       The Ray dashboard provides cluster introspection and job submission.\n       Recommend: restrict dashboard-host to localhost (127.0.0.1), add\n       network policy to limit pod-to-pod access, or place behind an\n       authenticated ingress before the next change window.\n\n[MEDIUM] Worker replicas scaled to 3 (baseline: 2) with no resource\n         limits set. Without CPU/memory limits, a single worker can\n         exhaust node resources. Recommend setting requests and limits\n         on ray-worker containers before further scaling.\n\n[LOW] No resource requests or limits on ray-head or ray-worker.\n      This predates the current changes but should be remediated.\n      Recommended baseline: cpu request 250m/limit 1, memory 512Mi/1Gi.\n\n[INFO] rollback-rehearsal ConfigMap is present and contains a tested\n       rollback script. Confirm it is removed or archived after the\n       change window closes to avoid confusion in future audits.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nEND OF AUDIT REPORT\nREPORT\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with full findings report"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2081,"cache_read_input_tokens":32087,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2081},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56ca1ff0-12ec-4848-b3d9-d8aba15eb721","uuid":"a46ef87b-f51f-4891-bd1a-67703301efc8","request_id":"req_011Cc6rn1dPXQ9pNL73E3fyk"}
